---
description: Keep client websites visually distinct while sharing UX quality
globs: apps/**/*.{ts,tsx,css}
alwaysApply: false
---

# Client Differentiation Guardrail

- Optimize for shared UX quality, not shared visual identity.
- Never reuse another client app's section composition, headline patterns, or component skin by default.
- Borrow only interaction logic and accessibility behavior from shared code.
- For new client pages, establish a unique visual direction in type scale, spacing rhythm, CTA treatment, image mood, and iconography style.
- If referencing an existing app, adapt structure and styling enough that the page does not feel template-derived.
